Description:
IMMACULATE MODERN STYLE HOME IN THE HEART OF GRANTVILLE
Set within a scenic country town of Grantville, this charming home with country views has a comfortable & spacious open plane kitchen area with breakfast bar & dining area. There are 2 family living areas in the home both with reverse cycle heating and cooling and a woodfire in one.
Featuring 4 bedrooms all with BIR’s & master with walk in robe, generous main bathroom, large laundry. Loads of storage throughout the home, including an entertaining deck.
The home sits on a 981m block approx. and was only built approximately 2 years ago.
The property is tucked away from it all but conveniently surrounded by all amenities including Beach Trails, Public Transport, Cafes, Shops, Medical services & much more.
Easy access to some of the best schools in Bass Coast - Bass Valley Primary School and the new Early Childhood campus and all Secondary Schools in the surrounding areas.
This thriving community offers a great life style including great tourist events, Penguin parade, local vine yards and much more and is only 40 Minutes to the world-famous GP track.
This property is a must see if you are looking for a relaxed coastal rural life style. Located in the heart of the township of Grantville.

Description:
Exclusive Home
Nothing to do just move in. A 4 bedroom brick veneer home in White Hills Estate, Lang Lang. Has many features. 3 ½ year old home on 710m2 block. Separate formal lounge, spacious open plan kitchen, dining and family room. Electric ducted heating and cooling system. Beautiful kitchen with huge island bench. Walk in pantry, dishwasher, 900mm stove and built in convection microwave.
Master has walk in robe and ensuite with double vanity, shower and toilet. All bedrooms are good sized including wardrobes. Sliding glass doors from master and family rooms lead out to the huge alfresco area with bistro blinds and feature pebble paving.
An internal door from house leads out to the dual car garage under roof line with remote controlled door. Side gates to backyard with two tool sheds, established gardens and fruit trees watered with the new water tank.

Description:
3 Bedroom & Study on an Elevated Position
This 3 bedroom, plus study home on approx. 807m2 block. 18 months old and never been occupied. Double glazed windows gives the home a 6 star rating. Home features high ceilings and study, which can be used as a bedroom or another living area. The 2nd & 3rd bedrooms, include built in wardrobes. A Spacious laundry with bench space, overhead cupboards and a 2 door linen cupboard. Beautiful kitchen, walk in pantry, island bench, dishwasher, overhead cupboard and plenty of bench space, 900mm stove and 5 hotplates. Fan in family room and spacious open plan living. Master double vanities, double shower, separate toilet, walk in robes. 2nd bathroom with vanity, shower and bath.
Sliding doors to outside undercover decked alfresco area. Internal door from 2 car garage under roof line.

Description:
Home With Lots Of Extras
On an 1109m2 block 3 bedroom home, 2 large living arears. Formal lounge, second living area with wet sink and walk in storage room. Ceiling fan, timber look flooring. High ceilings, beautiful modern kitchen, large bench space, pot drawers, dishwasher, walk-in pantry, 5 burner gas stove, electric oven, overhead cupboards and down lights. Master with ensuite, plus his & hers wardrobes. Second bedroom with semi ensuite, bath, vanity and shower. Third bedroom includes built in wardrobe. Gas ducted heating, evaporative cooling, plus ducted vacuum system. Laundry with bench space, plus cupboards. Internal door from garage into house. Parking for caravan or boat, 8 x 4 independent power box. Double garage and workshop with another separate 2 car carport and 2 car garage under roof line. Outdoors there is an undercover pergola, BBQ area with bistro blinds. 4 water tanks, high electric gates on the front.

Description:
BUSINESS FOR SALE - BASS COAST STOCK FEED!
Here is a great opportunity for extra family income and with huge potential for growth, this business offers:
- Visual highway exposure
- Located only metres off Bass Highway with a large amount of passing traffic
- Corner factory which gives extra car parking and delivery access
- Spacious floor area and plenty of shelving
- Office/kitchenette
- Lease 5 x 5
- Supportive local community
- Many hobby farms and horse properties surround
- Currently open 5 1/2 days per week
With no competition in the surrounding area and due to the growing population in the Bass Coast Shire, this business especially in the pet supply area is booming and also with the choice of doing longer hours, or deliveries after work, it lends itself to more potential income.

Address: 489 Mount Wellington Road French Island VIC 3921
Description:
TICKS ALL THE BOXES
Ticks all the boxes
Waterviews, Acreage, Two Dwellings, No Council Rates, Under $1M
This brand new listing on 100 beautiful acres, was once a neighbour to Kylie Minogue, but lots of stars can still be seen from this 3-4 bedroom home with bonus separate bungalow.
Sitting proudly near Mt Wellington, the high point of French Island, the architecturally designed main home comprises 3 Bedrooms plus study or 4th bedroom, separate bathroom, master bedroom with ensuite bathroom and walk in robe. The open plan kitchen, dine and lounge is flooded with lots of natural light and has expansive northerly views over the pavilion-style entertaining deck, which also wraps around to the east for sunrise and to the west for spectacular sunsets. It also boasts a separate wc and laundry, two fireplaces, polished floorboards, beautiful feature ceilings, plenty of rainwater, large shed with carport and a fully off-grid energy system, including solar hot water. There are extensive views over the national park and beyond to the marine national park of Westernport Bay.
The 2 bedroom bungalow is unseen and completely private from the main home and offers potential as a rental, or as B&B accommodation. It comprises a north-facing deck, mezzanine, floorboards, open plan kitchen/lounge/dining room and its own entrance from Farm Road.
Be quick to secure this fine example of a versatile French Island property which will suit the astute buyer wanting to say goodbye to council rates and hello to the unique qualities of everything the very special French Island has to offer.

Description:
GOOD GRAZING OPPORTUNITY NEAR WESTERNPORT BAY
Approx. 100 acres of productive pastureland with sheltered boundaries. The property has 10 paddocks all of which have their own troughs and serviced by a central laneway. A machinery shed, hay shed, 6 holding pens, 4 stables/birthing bay, loading ramp and crush, dam, 36 metre deep bore, mains power and two road frontages all compliment the property. There is an elevated home site that capture picturesque rural views and glimpses of bay. The paddocks were supered in autumn and carry approximately 60 cattle comfortably. Located only minutes to sandy beach and only 15 km to San Remo, 34 km to Phillip Island and major shopping centre. If you are looking for a unique and peaceful location look no further.
This land can also be viewed on www.yourlandshop.com.au

Description:
COASTAL BLOCK - 20 MINUTES TO PHILLIP ISLAND
Situated on the Melbourne side of Grantville. This coastal block of 508sqm approx is ideal for building a permanent home, as it is within commuting distance of major towns in the area. Located on the coastal side of the highway with rural surroundings and the school bus and Vline stops are nearby. Local shops, which include the chemist and Bank which are only 3 minutes away, and the primary school and kindergarten approx 5 mins away. Pioneer Bay is NOT a swimming beach but is ideal for relaxing and taking the dog for a stroll along the beach.

Description:
COASTAL COMFORT ON LARGE CORNER BLOCK!!!
The relaxed style and location of this immaculate home makes it the perfect lifestyle from the hustle and bustle of city life. The delightful property comprises 3 good size bedrooms all with built in robes, open plan living, dining and kitchen, polished timber floors, wood heater, split system air conditioner and plenty of natural light, all of which enhance a wonderful homely feel. The family bathroom has a full bath, there is plenty of storage cupboards, a good size laundry and sunblinds. The established, low maintenance gardens with paved paths provide a picture perfect outlook from the living area and master bedroom, with some glimpses of water. Bring the boat and caravan as there is plenty of space for extra vehicles and also the property has a 4 car garage which is concreted and powered and consists of a shower and a toilet. Double size sliding gates gives easy access and the property is fully fenced. Situated on a large block of approx. 1,100m2, with potential to subdivide STCA, and in a sought after location near all facilities, this is a MUST TO INSPECT.
A 24 hour boat ramp is within a couple of minutes and also scenic coastal walks. Local shops with doctor, chemist, bank, ambulance depot and cafes approximately 7 minutes away and Phillip Island and major shopping centre approximately 25 minutes.
Easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway.

Description:
Pretty As A Picture
The first thing you see as you approach this lovely property is the traditional white picket fence and behind the fence is this beautifully presented Federation styled timber home.
This home has retained many of the features a home of this era holds, including high ceilings lined with baltic pine timber and timber flooring throughout.
The three bedrooms all have built in ‘robes, ceiling fans and baltic lined ceilings. The third bedroom has a feature ornate fireplace.
Formal lounge room also has an attractive ornate fireplace, mantel piece and baltic lined ceiling and walls with feature cornice and a reverse cycle split system.
Kitchen has been beautifully renovated but retains some of its original character, plenty of cupboard space, timber top benches, stainless gas oven, hotplates, dishwasher, ceramic floor tiles and rangehood.
Bathroom has a claw foot bath, corner shower and pedestal hand basin. The family room has French Glass doors that lead out to a large decked outdoor living area. 50% of this decked area is roofed for weather protection on the family barbeques. All of this is nestled under established shady trees. There is gated access to the spacious yard and steel lockup garage.

Description:
Grand Bayside Living
This superb 2 storey home, boasting breath-taking panoramic views of Westernport Bay and French Island sits at the end of a small private court and just metres from the beach. It will impress from the moment you step inside. With 4 well-sized bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, 2 living zones, 2 outdoor entertaining areas and a beautiful solar-heated, salt water and self-cleaning pool it has everything you would expect from such a prestigious location all set on a generous 1019sqm block (approx.)
Cleverly designed to make the most of its beautiful surroundings the top floor is mostly taken up by a spacious open plan kitchen, living and dining ingeniously showcasing the tranquil views through the oversized, tinted windows without jeopardizing your privacy, step out onto the balcony and watch the sun set over the water.
Downstairs you are greeted with a lavish master suite with fully-equipped walk-in robe, ensuite with double vanity plus a sauna/detox box. 3 remaining bedrooms are well sized and are serviced by a bright and spacious family bathroom. A formal lounge with beautiful doors opening to the first of 2 outdoor living areas. This one with a huge pergola for year-round shade sets the scene for barbecuing with family and friends. The second will leave you feeling like you are in your own private resort, surrounding the low-maintenance pool, sit back in the sun, relax on the deck, entertain friends or supervise the kids in comfort and style.
Additional features include: A second double lock-up garage, ceiling fans throughout, upstairs powder room and study nook, ducted heating, refrigerated cooling, and quality fixtures and fittings throughout.

Description:
100 METRES APPROX FROM CORINELLA BEACH – WELCOME TO 8 WRIGHT STREET CORINELLA
Private, spacious, stylish and clever are just some of the words that describe 8 Wright Street Corinella.
Imagine sipping a cocktail whilst reading a great novel, all from the comfort of your beach chair or day bed on this amazing deck.
No expense has been spared on this fantastic property which has been extensively renovated and modernised into a state of the art beach home.
The open plan design amplifies your indoor/outdoor lifestyle with sweeping views of blue water looking out to Western Port Bay from your front deck and the back deck offers a stunning leafy landscaped garden views.
The home offers,
Stunning open plan living upstairs Lounge & Kitchen with bifold doors to deck area.
Kitchen has plenty of cupboard space, Gas stove cooker, Dishwasher,
Two bedrooms upstairs, master being one, all with BIR’s and new carpet.
Bathroom upstairs, separate toilet. Down stairs there is a separate toilet and laundry and bathroom in one area.
Floating floor boards in lounge and kitchen area.
Down stairs third bedroom BIR’s and new carpet.
Split system A/C.
Upstairs wood fire Coonara with stunning stone backdrop.
Double door remote garage plus garden shed.
Solar elec and solar hot water – Means good savings on those energy bills!

Description:
Resort – Style Property Offering Expansive Indoor/Outdoor Living
This impressive property is spread over 1300m block approx. in a quiet area of Tenby Point and has been designed for expansive indoor and outdoor living.
Mature leafy gardens provide complete privacy at the front of the home which boasts a substantial entertaining area complete with in-ground pool and poolside bay views,cabana day bed, and an amazing barbecue area with a rock water wall feature. The barbecue area is under cover so you can entertain all year round.
Equally impressive is the main living, dining and kitchen zone with timber features.
The home enjoys a large upstairs area with wood fire, split system, kitchenet area, powder room, access to an amazing deck area on both sides of the home, with amazing water views. The upstairs can be used has a guest room, studio or a BnB, or just enjoy it for your self has an upstairs lounge and further entertaining area of the home. Further three bedrooms down stairs two being serviced by the main bathroom, one having BIR and one with a walk-in robe, and the master having an ensuite and BIR.
The Home Offers
Upstairs living area or studio with kitchenet, powder room.
Split system reverse cycle in all bedrooms and main living areas.
Kitchen open and spacious, plenty of cupboard space, dishwasher, and gas stove cooker.
Bathroom down stairs and separate powder room.
Large laundry with plenty of storage and a shower.
2 entertaining areas.
Work shed garage.
Carport x 2 cars.
Plenty of space for a boat and a caravan too.
Solar panels.
Buyers looking for a substantial and versatile home which can offer flexible living and outstanding entertaining should consider this impressive package.
Daniel & Tamara from @realty Bass Coast have the pleasure of presenting this magnificent property in Tenby Point

Description:
YOU Need to Buy Caldermeade!!
Looking for that lifestyle change? Looking for the country township feel? Look no further than this one. Situated on approximately 3 acres this homestead is crying out for a new owner.
The weatherboard country feel home from the outside provides a charming welcome as you enter the property. Once inside you are greeted to an almost completely renovated interior. The kitchen will be sure to impress with ample of cupboard and bench space. New appliances will have you cooking up a storm with stainless steel 900mm free standing oven. The country features are brought to the front with the large Coonarra open wood fireplace accompanying the meals and living zone. With a split system air con to provide comfort in the warmer months. Three separate bedrooms with master suite entailing a split system, walk in robe and ensuite. The second bedroom boasts a large retreat area with mirrored on the built-in robe and a split system air con. The third bedroom provides ample floor space, split system air con and an original open fireplace.
Moving outside there is a huge pitched roof pergola attached to the house with a timber deck base. The large driveway leads to the large 3 cars shed with workshop area as well as hot and cold water that can be used if you need to wash down horses.
Located approximately 20 minutes out of Pakenham you have the ultimate country feel to a property but not a long drive outside of suburbia where you have all the amenities you could need. Just 500m down the road the plans have just been approved for a brand new large sporting facility.
The charming town of Caldermeade does not see many properties become available so be sure to secure this one today as it will go quick.

Description:
Massive Block with views
This is a rare opportunity to secure a fantastic family home where your children can play and yours dogs can run. Almost a 1/4 of an acre of low maintenance gardens and lawns. This 3 bedroom home commands attention! The master bedroom has 2 double built in robes with centre entry to the semi ensuite that is complete with a corner spa bath, large shower and vanity.
The lounge is light and airy with views accross the garden.
The kitchen boast a large bank of timber cabinetry and heaps of bench space for preparation with double fridge cavity, a s/s oven, gas hotplates and dishwasher. The kitchen overlooks the spacious meals/family room which leads to the under cover entertaining deck. From the deck on a good day you can seen the water in the distance as you kick back and relax. The sunsets are superb during summer. This block offers enough space to easily park a caravan, boat, trucks or trailers at the rear of the property behind a secure colorbond fence with 2 lots of double gates. The double garage gives you a great storage area too.
Features of the property include ducted vacuum, ducted heating and split system air conditioning. Position of the property is perfect being just a short stroll to the supermarket, specialty shops and school. Easy access to the highway should you need to commute to work. This one will sell fast!!

Bayside Beauty
Beautifully presented home here set in the coastal township of Pioneer Bay. This lovely split level residence offers so many wonderful features & extras such as air conditioning & solar panels. There are 3 good sized bedrooms with ensuite to master, vogue style bathroom, good sized lounge & dining, an excellent kitchen complete with neutra stone bench tops and modern appliances including dishwasher. Description:
QUAINT COTTAGE OPPOSITE FORESHORE!
Charming 2 bedroom cedar cottage on attractive treed block approx.. 620 sq.m. Featuring living/ dining area with wood and gas heating, separate cosy kitchen, timber look vinyl flooring, bathroom and laundry combined, veranda along front, back veranda, single garage and the property is fully fenced. Phillip Island and major shopping centre within 25 mins and easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway.
